<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-10T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/37<hi rend="superscript">4/17</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-10T13:00:00-05:00">June 10, 1940—1 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:55
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>87. With reference to Department’s telegram No. 78, June 1, 1
                                    p.m. Showing himself very emphatically in favor of immediate
                                    action President Vincent has just asked most solicitously when
                                    Colonels Randolph and Del Valle will arrive.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>